---
// Not a Fit Section — Transparency section showing when NOT to hire
---

<section class="not-a-fit" id="not-a-fit">
  <div class="not-a-fit-container">
    <h2 class="not-a-fit-title fade-in">
      When NOT to Hire Us.
    </h2>

    <p class="not-a-fit-intro fade-in">
      Transparency isn't a marketing trick. It's our operating system.
      Here's when we're the wrong choice:
    </p>

    <div class="not-a-fit-grid">
      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <div class="not-a-fit-card fade-in">
        <h3 class="not-a-fit-card-title">"You need a chatbot."</h3>
        <p class="not-a-fit-card-body">
          If all you want is a customer support bot, there are faster, cheaper options.
          We build production AI for complex workflows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <div class="not-a-fit-card fade-in">
        <h3 class="not-a-fit-card-title">"You want a 200-slide transformation roadmap."</h3>
        <p class="not-a-fit-card-body">
          We ship code, not PowerPoints. If you need a strategy deck to convince your board before building anything, we're not the right fit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <div class="not-a-fit-card fade-in">
        <h3 class="not-a-fit-card-title">"Your data isn't ready."</h3>
        <p class="not-a-fit-card-body">
          AI without clean data is expensive theater. We'll help you assess readiness, but won't sell you a project that will fail.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 4 -->
      <div class="not-a-fit-card fade-in">
        <h3 class="not-a-fit-card-title">"You want to 'add AI' for the press release."</h3>
        <p class="not-a-fit-card-body">
          If AI doesn't solve a specific, measurable problem in your workflow, don't build it. We'll tell you that for free.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="not-a-fit-closing fade-in">
      Still here? Then we should talk.
    </p>

    <div class="not-a-fit-cta fade-in">
      <a href="#contact" class="btn-primary">
        Get in touch →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .not-a-fit {
    padding: 8rem 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .not-a-fit-container {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .not-a-fit-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 2.625rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--white-pure);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .not-a-fit-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-light);
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
  }

  .not-a-fit-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .not-a-fit-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    .not-a-fit-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(200, 170, 80, 0.15);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }
  }

  .not-a-fit-card-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold-warm);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .not-a-fit-card-body {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-light);
  }

  .not-a-fit-closing {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--white-warm);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .not-a-fit-cta {
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .not-a-fit {
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .not-a-fit-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .not-a-fit-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Intersection Observer for fade-in
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.not-a-fit .fade-in').forEach(el => {
    observer.observe(el);
  });
</script>
